     The Quad ministers' meeting
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-secretary-marco-rubio-quad-meeting-washington.jpg" alt="US Secretary of State Marco Rubio met his counterparts in Washington, DC, despite strained ties between the Quad nations and the US" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
           US Secretary of State Marco Rubio met his counterparts in Washington, DC, despite strained ties between the Quad nations and the US. Credits: Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       The Quad, a diplomatic partnership between the US, India, Japan, and Australia, has launched an initiative <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-focused-on-securing-critical-minerals?source=website" target="_blank">focused on securing critical minerals</a>, aiming to reduce reliance on China’s dominant supply chains. These minerals are essential for modern technologies, such as semiconductors.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    This initiative is part of a broader <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-economic-and-strategic-cooperation?source=website" target="_blank">economic and strategic cooperation</a>. It includes deepening maritime law enforcement through regional training and cooperation with the Coast Guard. They are also establishing an Indo-Pacific Logistics Network to improve the response to natural disasters. Parallel to this, they will launch the Port of Future Partnerships in Mumbai, aiming to modernize port infrastructure in the Indo-Pacific region. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
     The group further addressed the threats posed by North Korea’s missile and nuclear programs, cybercrime, and arms proliferation. They condemned all acts of terrorism and violent extremism, including the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-pahalgam-attack?source=website" target="_blank">Pahalgam attack</a>, and pledged justice for victims. However, the Quad avoided any direct reference to Pakistan. </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
    In a show of regional solidarity, they collectively contributed $30M in humanitarian assistance to support communities affected by the earthquake in central Myanmar. The Quad reaffirmed its strong support for ASEAN’s efforts to force an effective implementation of the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h1-4-five-point-consensus?source=website" target="_blank">Five Point Consensus</a> in seeking an inclusive, durable, and peaceful resolution to the crisis in Myanmar. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
