          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
        Indictment over fascist propaganda</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
     Summary: Călin Georgescu was indicted for endorsing fascist propaganda while he remains under investigation for other offenses. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Former Romanian Presidential candidate Călin Georgescu has been indicted for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-promoting-fascist-propaganda?source=website" target="_blank">promoting fascist propaganda</a>. Prosecutors allege that between June 2020 to May 2025, he repeatedly endorsed fascist ideas through a series of interviews, online posts, and public speeches. They also accused him of glorifying extremist historical figures such as Marshal Ion Antonescu, the leader of Romania’s World War II fascist government, and Corneliu Zelea Codreanu, the founder of Romania’s interwar Iron Guard. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The charges focus on “legionary propaganda” associated with Romania’s short-lived <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-national-legionary-state?source=website" target="_blank">National Legionary State</a> (1940–1941). If convicted, Georgescu faces up to three years in prison. He is also under investigation for allegedly attempting to overthrow <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h2-7-romania-s-constitutional-governance?source=website" target="_blank">Romania’s constitutional governance</a> by engaging in currency laundering, bribing voters, and computer fraud in connection with Romania’s canceled presidential election.
       </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       A far-right nationalist and EU-NATO critic, Georgescu gained traction in Romania’s annulled 2024 presidential election, earning nearly 23% of the vote. The result was invalidated over evidence of Russian interference and <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-spotlight-h2-8-tiktok-disinformation?source=website" target="_blank">TikTok disinformation</a>. Barred from the rescheduled May vote, Georgescu withdrew from politics.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

