        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇫🇯 Fiji - Says no to the Chinese military.</strong> 
           Fiji’s PM Sitiveni Rabuka said China’s military presence is not welcome in the South Pacific, calling for the region to remain peaceful and devoid of superpower rivalries. While acknowledging China’s development aid, Rabuka emphasized it should not affect ties with Australia, New Zealand, or the US, urging balanced diplomacy without compromising regional stability (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-worldwide-13-friends-with-all?source=website" target="_blank">friends with all</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇮🇳 India - Dalai Lama confirms successor.</strong> 
          The Dalai Lama confirmed that the institution of the Dalai Lama will continue after his death, with the Gaden Phodrang Trust in India, exclusively recognizing his successor. Meanwhile, Tibetans reject China’s involvement, fearing political manipulation of the succession process (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-worldwide-14-reincarnation-drama?source=website" target="_blank">reincarnation drama</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇩🇰 Denmark - Assumes the EU presidency.</strong> 
           Denmark has assumed the EU Council presidency, with security and competitiveness as its top priorities amid growing global uncertainty. Their presidency will focus on defense spending, preserving the Green Agreement, and advancing migration policies, including its restrictive model (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-worldwide-15-unprecedented-times?source=website" target="_blank">unprecedented times</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇦🇺 Australia - Aboriginal genocide.</strong> 
          The Yoorrook Justice Commission in Australia has concluded that British colonists committed genocide against Indigenous Australians. They detailed the impact of violence, disease, and cultural destruction, which reduced the Indigenous population by 75% within two decades. The report includes recommendations for reparations, education reforms, and an apology to excluded Aboriginal soldiers (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-worldwide-16-chilling-details?source=website" target="_blank">chilling details</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇩🇪 Germany - Mutual Defense with UK.</strong> 
         The US and Germany are set to sign a treaty on July 17, which focuses on defense, economic growth, and security cooperation. This pact includes a mutual assistance clause in the event of threats. It will also address migration, research, innovation, and cross-border exchanges, with a specific focus on youth mobility (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-3-jul-25-worldwide-17-german-british-exchange?source=website" target="_blank">German-British exchange</a>). 
          </p>
          
